Level 1: Beginner
1. EBS Snapshot Cleanup (delete >30 days) - S3 trigger + CloudWatch Events
2. Start/Stop EC2 on Schedule (9 AM IST to 8 PM IST) - EventBridge cron
3. AMI Backup with 7-Day Retention - DescribeImages + deregister old
4. Auto-tag Unattached EBS Volumes - Filter available status + create tags
5. Send S3 Upload Notification to Slack - S3 event + webhook

Level 2: Intermediate
6. Copy AMI to DR Region (ap-south-1 to ap-southeast-1) - Cross-region replication
7. Rotate RDS TLS Certificates Automatically - Modify DB instance + SNS notify
8. Scale EBS Volume IOPS Dynamically (gp2→gp3 based on CloudWatch alarm)
9. Remediate Security Groups (remove open 0.0.0.0/22) - Auto-revoke bad rules
10. Create AMI from Instance ID via SNS ChatOps - SNS trigger + Lambda

Level 3: Advanced
11. EBS Volume Auto-Resize from CloudWatch (80% threshold reached)
12. Lambda in VPC to access RDS Private Subnet - ENI + Security Group config
13. Dead Letter Queue (SQS) for failed snapshot copy operations
14. Reserved Concurrency to prevent runaway Lambda costs
15. AWS X-Ray Tracing for EBS/AMI backup workflows

Level 4: Expert
16. Step Functions orchestration: Snapshot → Copy → Create Volume → Attach → Verify
17. Secrets Manager rotation for EC2 MySQL credentials (Lambda rotation function)
18. Provisioned Concurrency for backup-critical Lambda (zero cold start)
19. AWS SAM deployment with CodeDeploy Canary (10% traffic shift)
20. Multi-region Disaster Recovery Lambda (active-passive with Route53 failover)
